general.name: specFull
general.short: BOSS Spectro Redux spectrum file (full version)
general.description:
The spec-PLATE-MJD-FIBER.fits files contain a repackaging of all spectral data for a given plugging (plate, mjd, fiber), including both the coadded spectrum and optionally the individual exposure frames. This groups the information from spFrame, spCFrame, spFlat, spPlate, spZbest, spZline, and spAll so that for each object one only needs to read a single file. 
     HDU 0  : Header info from spPlate     HDU 1  : Coadded spectrum from spPlate     HDU 2  : Summary metadata copied from spAll     HDU 3  : Line fitting metadata from spZline     HDU 4+ : [Optional] Individual spCFrame spectra [B, R for each exposure]
A "lite" version of these files also exists in the "lite" subdirectory tree. These contain HDUS 0-3, but do not have the individual frame data and thus are much smaller.

surveys.name: BHM
surveys.description: An optical time-domain spectroscopic survey of quasars and X-ray sources

surveys.name: BOSS
surveys.description: An optical spectroscopic survey mapping the spatial distribution of LRGs and quasars to detect the scale of baryon acoustic oscillations

surveys.name: eBOSS
surveys.description: A cosmological survey of quasars and galaxies to understand baryon acoustic oscillations

general.naming_convention: spec-[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{5}-[0-9]{4}\.fits, where [0-9]{4} is a zero-padded, four-digit number containing the plate number, [0-9]{5} is a five-digit number containing the MJD number and [0-9]{4} is a four-digit number containing the fiber id.

changelog.description: Describes changes to the datamodel product and/or file structure from one release to another

hdu0.name: PRIMARY
hdu0.description:
Copied from spPlate with the following additions/modifications:
  • PLUG_RA, PLUG_DEC, THING_ID, FIBERID: added from spAll
  • NEXP and EXPID*: modified to just include the frames which contributed to this fiber
  • Removed keywords which apply only to single exposures

model.name: MODEL
model.description: pipeline best model fit used for classification and redshift

hdu2.description: BOSS spectra: copy of row from spAll for this (plate, mjd, fiber) SDSS-I/-II spectra: copy of row from specObj for this (plate, mjd, fiber)

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu0.name: PRIMARY
hdu0.description:
Copied from spPlate with the following additions/modifications:
  • PLUG_RA, PLUG_DEC, THING_ID, FIBERID: added from spAll
  • NEXP and EXPID*: modified to just include the frames which contributed to this fiber
  • Removed keywords which apply only to single exposures

header.value: FITS (Flexible Image Transport System) format is defined in 'Astronomy

wdisp.name: WDISP
wdisp.description: Wavelength dispersion (sigma of fitted Gaussian) in units of number of pixel

model.name: MODEL
model.description: pipeline best model fit used for classification and redshift

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu0.name: PRIMARY
hdu0.description:
Copied from spPlate with the following additions/modifications:
  • PLUG_RA, PLUG_DEC, THING_ID, FIBERID: added from spAll
  • NEXP and EXPID*: modified to just include the frames which contributed to this fiber
  • Removed keywords which apply only to single exposures

wdisp.name: WDISP
wdisp.description: Wavelength dispersion (sigma of fitted Gaussian) in units of number of pixel

model.name: MODEL
model.description: pipeline best model fit used for classification and redshift

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu0.name: PRIMARY
hdu0.description:
Copied from spPlate with the following additions/modifications:
  • PLUG_RA, PLUG_DEC, THING_ID, FIBERID: added from spAll
  • NEXP and EXPID*: modified to just include the frames which contributed to this fiber
  • Removed keywords which apply only to single exposures

wdisp.description: Wavelength dispersion (sigma of fitted Gaussian) in units of number of pixel

model.description: pipeline best model fit used for classification and redshift

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

hdu4.name: B1-00104927-00104934-00104935
hdu4.description: For each exposure there is one HDU for the red camera and one for the blue. These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)

These are in the order of the EXPIDnn keywords in the HDU 0 header, and their EXTNAME keywords match the EXPIDnn keywords from HDU 0. Required Header Keywords: Taken from spCFrame files. BOSS spectra have the addition of YPIX0 defining the y-pixel location of the first flux bin. Binary table with columns:

calib.name: CALIB
calib.description: conversion between flux and electrons: flux = electrons*calib

x.name: X
x.description: x-pixel location of trace on CCD (BOSS spectra only)
